summary:
Emphasizes importance of access to reports and information on UNDOF's configuration; 

Underscores need for UNDOF to have necessary means and resources; 

Expresses appreciation to UNDOF personnel, condemns incidents threatening their safety; 

Welcomes efforts to enhance UNDOF's safety and security.
The Security Council:

3. strongly calls on the Syrian armed opposition groups to halt activities endangering UN peacekeepers and allow UN personnel to carry out their mandate safely;

4. calls on all groups to abandon UNDOF positions, return peacekeepers' vehicles, weapons, and equipment, and vacate the Quneitra crossing point;

5. demands cooperation with UNDOF operations, respect for its privileges and immunities, and ensures freedom of movement and security for UN personnel;

6. recognizes the need for temporary procedures for UNDOF personnel to cross between Alpha and Bravo sides, urges parties to engage with UNDOF, and re-open the Quneitra crossing when security permits;

7. welcomes UNDOF's efforts to implement the zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, and urges troop-contributing countries to investigate and punish related acts;

8. renews UNDOF's mandate for six months until 30 June 2016 and requests the Secretary-General to ensure UNDOF has required capacity and resources;

9. requests the Secretary-General to report every 90 days on developments and measures to implement resolution 338 (1973);

10. requests an assessment of UNDOF's equipment, resources, and requirements to maximize effectiveness and a strategy for augmenting capabilities.
